commit.message:
pyobjc_setup.py: sdk detection fixes

Detect correct SDK when an -isysroot flag is given in CFLAGS in the
environment, overriding any that may be in sysconfig. Support alternate
form of -isysroot where there is no space between the flag and the
associated path. Don't try to extract a version from the filename of
'MacOSX.sdk'; instead get the version from its SDKSettings.plist.

Issue #300: Fix SystemError in block edge case

PyObjC raised a SystemError when converting a callable into
an ObjC block when the callable is a bound method without
positional arguments.

Some changes to enable building on macOS 10.14

My 10.14 VM has a version of Xcode 11 with the 10.15
SDK, but without all of the latest symbols.
Issue 299: PubSub bindings won't build on 10.15, but "pyobjc" package still tries to install it.
Update version to 6.2.1b1
